1239.description:
Service: Authentication
Feature: JWT Tokens
Activity: User session management

**ISSUE:**

Users logged out every 15 minutes. JWT access tokens expiring too quickly. No refresh token mechanism. Users must re-enter credentials frequently. Poor user experience.

Complaint: "Why do I have to log in every 15 minutes?"

**SYMPTOMS:**
→ Access token expiry: 15 minutes
→ No refresh token
→ Users logged out frequently
→ Poor UX
→ Security vs usability tradeoff
→ Mobile app especially affected
→ Long-running operations interrupted

**COMPONENTS:**
JWT token generation, authentication service, token validation

---

**ROOT CAUSE:**

JWT access tokens set to expire after 15 minutes for security. No refresh token mechanism implemented. Users forced to re-authenticate every 15 minutes. Security-focused design didn't consider UX.

Current flow:
1. User logs in
2. Receives JWT (expires in 15 min)
3. After 15 min, token invalid
4. All API calls return 401
5. User must log in again

**FIX:**

Implemented refresh token:

```python
# BEFORE - Only access token:
from flask_jwt_extended import create_access_token

@app.route('/login', methods=['POST'])
def login():
    username = request.json.get('username')
    password = request.json.get('password')

    if verify_password(username, password):
        access_token = create_access_token(
            identity=username,
            expires_delta=timedelta(minutes=15)
        )
        return jsonify(access_token=access_token)

    return jsonify(error='Invalid credentials'), 401

# AFTER - Access + refresh tokens:
from flask_jwt_extended import (
    create_access_token,
    create_refresh_token,
    jwt_required,
    get_jwt_identity
)

@app.route('/login', methods=['POST'])
def login():
    username = request.json.get('username')
    password = request.json.get('password')

    if verify_password(username, password):
        access_token = create_access_token(
            identity=username,
            expires_delta=timedelta(minutes=15)  # Short-lived
        )
        refresh_token = create_refresh_token(
            identity=username,
            expires_delta=timedelta(days=30)  # Long-lived
        )

        return jsonify(
            access_token=access_token,
            refresh_token=refresh_token
        )

    return jsonify(error='Invalid credentials'), 401

@app.route('/refresh', methods=['POST'])
@jwt_required(refresh=True)
def refresh():
    current_user = get_jwt_identity()

    # Generate new access token
    new_access_token = create_access_token(
        identity=current_user,
        expires_delta=timedelta(minutes=15)
    )

    return jsonify(access_token=new_access_token)
```

Implemented token rotation:

```python
import redis

redis_client = redis.Redis()

@app.route('/refresh', methods=['POST'])
@jwt_required(refresh=True)
def refresh():
    current_user = get_jwt_identity()
    jti = get_jwt()['jti']  # JWT ID

    # Check if refresh token already used
    if redis_client.get(f'used_refresh:{jti}'):
        # Refresh token reuse detected - possible attack
        revoke_all_tokens(current_user)
        return jsonify(error='Token reuse detected'), 401

    # Mark refresh token as used
    redis_client.setex(f'used_refresh:{jti}', 2592000, '1')  # 30 days

    # Generate new tokens
    new_access_token = create_access_token(identity=current_user)
    new_refresh_token = create_refresh_token(identity=current_user)

    return jsonify(
        access_token=new_access_token,
        refresh_token=new_refresh_token
    )
```

Client-side automatic refresh:

```javascript
// Frontend - Automatic token refresh
class AuthService {
    constructor() {
        this.accessToken = localStorage.getItem('access_token');
        this.refreshToken = localStorage.getItem('refresh_token');
        this.refreshTimer = null;
    }

    async login(username, password) {
        const response = await fetch('/login', {
            method: 'POST',
            headers: {'Content-Type': 'application/json'},
            body: JSON.stringify({username, password})
        });

        const data = await response.json();

        this.accessToken = data.access_token;
        this.refreshToken = data.refresh_token;

        localStorage.setItem('access_token', this.accessToken);
        localStorage.setItem('refresh_token', this.refreshToken);

        // Schedule token refresh before expiry
        this.scheduleRefresh();
    }

    scheduleRefresh() {
        // Refresh 1 minute before expiry (14 minutes)
        const refreshIn = 14 * 60 * 1000;

        this.refreshTimer = setTimeout(() => {
            this.refreshAccessToken();
        }, refreshIn);
    }

    async refreshAccessToken() {
        try {
            const response = await fetch('/refresh', {
                method: 'POST',
                headers: {
                    'Authorization': `Bearer ${this.refreshToken}`
                }
            });

            const data = await response.json();

            this.accessToken = data.access_token;
            this.refreshToken = data.refresh_token;

            localStorage.setItem('access_token', this.accessToken);
            localStorage.setItem('refresh_token', this.refreshToken);

            // Schedule next refresh
            this.scheduleRefresh();
        } catch (error) {
            // Refresh failed, force re-login
            this.logout();
        }
    }

    logout() {
        clearTimeout(this.refreshTimer);
        localStorage.removeItem('access_token');
        localStorage.removeItem('refresh_token');
        window.location.href = '/login';
    }
}
```

Implemented token revocation:

```python
@app.route('/logout', methods=['POST'])
@jwt_required()
def logout():
    jti = get_jwt()['jti']

    # Revoke access token
    redis_client.setex(f'revoked:{jti}', 900, '1')  # 15 minutes

    return jsonify(message='Logged out successfully')

# Token validation
@jwt.token_in_blocklist_loader
def check_if_token_revoked(jwt_header, jwt_payload):
    jti = jwt_payload['jti']
    return redis_client.get(f'revoked:{jti}') is not None
```

