1584.description:
**CALENDAR EVENTS DISPLAYING IN WRONG TIMEZONE**

### Problem
Calendar events created in one timezone display at incorrect times in calendar view.

### Example
```
Event Created:
  Title: "Team Meeting"
  Time: 2:00 PM PST (14:00)
  Date: Feb 6, 2026

Calendar Display:
  Shows: 10:00 PM PST (22:00) ✗
  Should show: 2:00 PM PST (14:00) ✓

Difference: +8 hours
```

### Root Cause Analysis

**Issue 1: UTC Conversion Applied Twice**
```javascript
// WRONG - Converting to UTC twice
const eventTime = new Date('2026-02-06T14:00:00-08:00');  // 2pm PST
const utcTime = eventTime.toISOString();  // Converts to UTC: 22:00
const displayTime = new Date(utcTime + 'Z');  // Treats as UTC again!
// Result: 22:00 PST (10pm) - 8 hours off!

// CORRECT - Convert once
const eventTime = new Date('2026-02-06T14:00:00-08:00');
const displayTime = eventTime;  // Already in correct timezone
```

**Issue 2: Timezone Offset Wrong Direction**
```javascript
// WRONG - Applying offset in wrong direction
const utcTime = '2026-02-06T22:00:00Z';  // 10pm UTC = 2pm PST
const offset = -8;  // PST is UTC-8
const localTime = new Date(utcTime);
localTime.setHours(localTime.getHours() + offset);  // ✗ Subtracts 8!
// Result: 2pm UTC = 6am PST (wrong!)

// CORRECT - Let JavaScript handle it
const utcTime = '2026-02-06T22:00:00Z';
const localTime = new Date(utcTime);
// Automatically converts to local timezone
```

**Issue 3: Storing Time Without Timezone**
```javascript
// WRONG - Ambiguous time storage
const eventData = {
    date: '2026-02-06',
    time: '14:00'  // ✗ No timezone info!
};

// CORRECT - Store with timezone or as UTC
const eventData = {
    datetime: '2026-02-06T14:00:00-08:00',  // ISO 8601 with timezone
    timezone: 'America/Los_Angeles'
};

// OR store as UTC
const eventData = {
    datetime_utc: '2026-02-06T22:00:00Z',  // UTC
    timezone: 'America/Los_Angeles'  // For display
};
```

### Complete Solution

**Data Model**
```javascript
class CalendarEvent {
    constructor(data) {
        this.id = data.id;
        this.title = data.title;
        this.description = data.description;

        // Store as UTC timestamp
        this.startTimeUTC = new Date(data.start_time);
        this.endTimeUTC = new Date(data.end_time);

        // Store original timezone
        this.timezone = data.timezone || Intl.DateTimeFormat().resolvedOptions().timeZone;
    }

    // Get start time in user's local timezone
    getLocalStartTime() {
        return this.startTimeUTC;
    }

    // Get start time in specific timezone
    getStartTimeInTimezone(timezone) {
        return new Date(this.startTimeUTC.toLocaleString('en-US', {
            timeZone: timezone
        }));
    }

    // Format for display
    formatTime(timezone = null) {
        const tz = timezone || this.timezone;

        return this.startTimeUTC.toLocaleString('en-US', {
            timeZone: tz,
            year: 'numeric',
            month: 'short',
            day: 'numeric',
            hour: 'numeric',
            minute: '2-digit',
            hour12: true
        });
    }
}
```

**Calendar Display**
```javascript
class Calendar {
    constructor(containerId) {
        this.container = document.getElementById(containerId);
        this.currentDate = new Date();
        this.events = [];
        this.userTimezone = Intl.DateTimeFormat().resolvedOptions().timeZone;
    }

    async loadEvents(year, month) {
        const response = await fetch(
            `/api/calendar/events?year=${year}&month=${month}`
        );
        const data = await response.json();

        this.events = data.events.map(e => new CalendarEvent(e));
        this.render();
    }

    render() {
        const year = this.currentDate.getFullYear();
        const month = this.currentDate.getMonth();

        // Get first and last day of month
        const firstDay = new Date(year, month, 1);
        const lastDay = new Date(year, month + 1, 0);

        let html = '<div class="calendar">';
        html += this.renderHeader(year, month);
        html += this.renderDays(firstDay, lastDay);
        html += '</div>';

        this.container.innerHTML = html;
        this.attachEventListeners();
    }

    renderHeader(year, month) {
        const monthNames = [
            'January', 'February', 'March', 'April', 'May', 'June',
            'July', 'August', 'September', 'October', 'November', 'December'
        ];

        return `
            <div class="calendar-header">
                <button class="prev-month">‹</button>
                <h2>${monthNames[month]} ${year}</h2>
                <button class="next-month">›</button>
            </div>
            <div class="day-names">
                <div>Sun</div><div>Mon</div><div>Tue</div>
                <div>Wed</div><div>Thu</div><div>Fri</div><div>Sat</div>
            </div>
        `;
    }

    renderDays(firstDay, lastDay) {
        let html = '<div class="calendar-grid">';

        // Empty cells before month starts
        const startDayOfWeek = firstDay.getDay();
        for (let i = 0; i < startDayOfWeek; i++) {
            html += '<div class="calendar-day empty"></div>';
        }

        // Days of month
        const daysInMonth = lastDay.getDate();
        for (let day = 1; day <= daysInMonth; day++) {
            const date = new Date(firstDay.getFullYear(), firstDay.getMonth(), day);
            const dayEvents = this.getEventsForDate(date);

            html += `<div class="calendar-day" data-date="${date.toISOString()}">`;
            html += `<div class="day-number">${day}</div>`;
            html += '<div class="day-events">';

            dayEvents.forEach(event => {
                const startTime = event.getLocalStartTime();
                const timeStr = startTime.toLocaleTimeString('en-US', {
                    hour: 'numeric',
                    minute: '2-digit',
                    hour12: true
                });

                html += `
                    <div class="event" data-event-id="${event.id}">
                        <span class="event-time">${timeStr}</span>
                        <span class="event-title">${event.title}</span>
                    </div>
                `;
            });

            html += '</div></div>';
        }

        html += '</div>';
        return html;
    }

    getEventsForDate(date) {
        // Get events that occur on this date in user's timezone
        const dayStart = new Date(date);
        dayStart.setHours(0, 0, 0, 0);

        const dayEnd = new Date(date);
        dayEnd.setHours(23, 59, 59, 999);

        return this.events.filter(event => {
            const eventTime = event.getLocalStartTime();
            return eventTime >= dayStart && eventTime <= dayEnd;
        });
    }

    attachEventListeners() {
        // Month navigation
        this.container.querySelector('.prev-month').addEventListener('click', () => {
            this.currentDate.setMonth(this.currentDate.getMonth() - 1);
            this.loadEvents(this.currentDate.getFullYear(), this.currentDate.getMonth());
        });

        this.container.querySelector('.next-month').addEventListener('click', () => {
            this.currentDate.setMonth(this.currentDate.getMonth() + 1);
            this.loadEvents(this.currentDate.getFullYear(), this.currentDate.getMonth());
        });

        // Event clicks
        this.container.querySelectorAll('.event').forEach(el => {
            el.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
                const eventId = e.currentTarget.dataset.eventId;
                this.showEventDetails(eventId);
            });
        });
    }

    showEventDetails(eventId) {
        const event = this.events.find(e => e.id === eventId);
        if (!event) return;

        const modal = document.createElement('div');
        modal.className = 'event-modal';
        modal.innerHTML = `
            <div class="modal-content">
                <h3>${event.title}</h3>
                <p><strong>Time:</strong> ${event.formatTime()}</p>
                <p><strong>Timezone:</strong> ${event.timezone}</p>
                <p><strong>Your time:</strong> ${event.formatTime(this.userTimezone)}</p>
                <p>${event.description || ''}</p>
                <button class="close-modal">Close</button>
            </div>
        `;

        document.body.appendChild(modal);

        modal.querySelector('.close-modal').addEventListener('click', () => {
            modal.remove();
        });
    }
}

// Initialize
const calendar = new Calendar('calendar-container');
calendar.loadEvents(
    new Date().getFullYear(),
    new Date().getMonth()
);
```

**Backend (Python/Django)**
```python
from django.http import JsonResponse
from django.utils import timezone
import pytz
from datetime import datetime

def get_calendar_events(request):
    year = int(request.GET.get('year'))
    month = int(request.GET.get('month'))

    # Get events for month
    start_date = datetime(year, month, 1, tzinfo=pytz.UTC)
    if month == 12:
        end_date = datetime(year + 1, 1, 1, tzinfo=pytz.UTC)
    else:
        end_date = datetime(year, month + 1, 1, tzinfo=pytz.UTC)

    events = CalendarEvent.objects.filter(
        start_time__gte=start_date,
        start_time__lt=end_date
    )

    # Serialize events
    events_data = []
    for event in events:
        events_data.append({
            'id': event.id,
            'title': event.title,
            'description': event.description,
            'start_time': event.start_time.isoformat(),  # ISO 8601 with timezone
            'end_time': event.end_time.isoformat(),
            'timezone': event.timezone
        })

    return JsonResponse({'events': events_data})

def create_event(request):
    data = json.loads(request.body)

    # Parse datetime with timezone
    start_time = datetime.fromisoformat(data['start_time'])
    end_time = datetime.fromisoformat(data['end_time'])

    # Ensure timezone-aware
    if start_time.tzinfo is None:
        tz = pytz.timezone(data.get('timezone', 'UTC'))
        start_time = tz.localize(start_time)
        end_time = tz.localize(end_time)

    # Create event
    event = CalendarEvent.objects.create(
        title=data['title'],
        description=data.get('description', ''),
        start_time=start_time,
        end_time=end_time,
        timezone=data.get('timezone', 'UTC'),
        created_by=request.user
    )

    return JsonResponse({
        'id': event.id,
        'start_time': event.start_time.isoformat()
    })
```

