**PRINT PREVIEW SHOWING BLANK PAGE**

### Problem
Print preview displays blank page instead of report content. Screen display works fine.

### Root Causes

**1. Missing Print Media Query**
```css
/* WRONG - Content hidden for print */
.report-content {
    display: block;
}

@media print {
    /* Missing! Content not shown for print */
}

/* CORRECT - Explicit print styles */
@media print {
    .report-content {
        display: block !important;
        visibility: visible !important;
    }
}
```

**2. Display: None on Print**
```css
/* WRONG - Hiding content for print */
body {
    display: flex;  /* Flex layout */
}

@media print {
    body {
        display: none;  /* ✗ Hides everything! */
    }
}

/* CORRECT */
@media print {
    body {
        display: block;  /* ✓ Show for print */
    }
}
```

**3. Absolute Positioning Off-Page**
```css
/* WRONG - Content positioned off page */
.report-content {
    position: absolute;
    left: -9999px;  /* ✗ Hidden off-screen */
}

@media print {
    /* Forgot to reset position! */
}

/* CORRECT */
@media print {
    .report-content {
        position: static;
        left: auto;
    }
}
```

**4. Height: 0 or Overflow: Hidden**
```css
/* WRONG - Zero height container */
.print-container {
    height: 0;
    overflow: hidden;
}

/* CORRECT */
@media print {
    .print-container {
        height: auto;
        overflow: visible;
    }
}
```

